---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="OPSEC — SWAMP PAY" description="How SWAMP PAY eliminates surveillance from payment processing. Zero data retention. On-device encryption.">
  <section class="relative min-h-[60vh] overflow-hidden border-b border-olive/20 bg-midnight pt-24 pb-24">
    <img
      src="/hangingOut.jpg"
      alt=""
      class="war-photo-bg-hero"
      loading="eager"
      aria-hidden="true"
    />
    <div class="war-photo-overlay" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="film-grain absolute inset-0 z-[2]" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-4">
        <span class="stamp-classified text-xs text-napalm">Classified</span>
        <span class="h-px flex-1 bg-khaki/20" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-stencil text-5xl tracking-wide text-white sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl">
        Anti-Surveillance<br />
        <span class="text-phosphor crt-glow">by Design</span>.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-bone/90">
        SWAMP PAY doesn't need to protect your data — because it never collects it.
        This is OPSEC through architecture, not policy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-b border-olive/20 bg-bunker py-24" aria-label="The problem">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="grid gap-16 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label-military">Intelligence Brief — The Enemy</p>
          <h2 class="font-stencil text-3xl text-white">
            The surveillance <span class="text-amber crt-glow-amber">economy</span>.
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-smoke">
            Every card swipe feeds a global surveillance apparatus. Payment processors
            build consumer profiles, sell behavioral data, and enable warrantless
            financial surveillance. Your purchase history is not your own. They are
            running recon on every transaction.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="terminal-border rounded-lg bg-midnight/60 p-8">
          <p class="mb-4 font-stencil text-xs text-amber">THREAT ASSESSMENT — TRADITIONAL PAYMENT DATA</p>
          <div class="space-y-2 font-mono text-sm text-smoke">
            <p><span class="text-amber">→</span> Card number transmitted to processor</p>
            <p><span class="text-amber">→</span> Transaction logged with timestamp + location</p>
            <p><span class="text-amber">→</span> Customer profile updated</p>
            <p><span class="text-amber">→</span> Behavioral data sold to advertisers</p>
            <p><span class="text-amber">→</span> Purchase history available to government</p>
            <p><span class="text-amber">→</span> Data retained for 7+ years</p>
            <div class="mt-4 border-t border-amber/20 pt-4">
              <p class="text-napalm font-stencil">EXPOSURE LEVEL: <span class="font-bold">TOTAL COMPROMISE</span></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-olive/20 bg-midnight py-24" aria-label="Our approach">
    <img
      src="/vietnamePic.jpg"
      alt=""
      class="war-photo-bg"
      style="object-position: center 70%;"
      loading="lazy"
      aria-hidden="true"
    />
    <div class="war-photo-overlay" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <p class="section-label-military">Countermeasures — SWAMP Architecture</p>
      <h2 class="font-stencil text-3xl text-white">
        SWAMP PAY <span class="text-phosphor crt-glow">OPSEC</span>.
      </h2>

      <div class="mt-16 grid gap-px bg-olive/15 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="bg-midnight p-8">
          <p class="font-stencil text-4xl text-olive/30">01</p>
          <h3 class="mt-4 font-stencil text-xl text-white">On-Device Processing</h3>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-smoke">
            All transaction logic executes within the terminal's secure enclave.
            Card data, wallet addresses, and transaction amounts never leave the device
            in plaintext. Like a sealed field radio — nothing leaks.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-midnight p-8">
          <p class="font-stencil text-4xl text-olive/30">02</p>
          <h3 class="mt-4 font-stencil text-xl text-white">Ephemeral Data Model</h3>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-smoke">
            Transaction records exist only long enough to confirm settlement.
            Once confirmed, all customer-identifying data is cryptographically
            shredded. No logs, no profiles, no trail.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-midnight p-8">
          <p class="font-stencil text-4xl text-olive/30">03</p>
          <h3 class="mt-4 font-stencil text-xl text-white">Zero-Knowledge Settlement</h3>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-smoke">
            Settlement data contains only the minimum information required: amount
            and destination. No customer identity, no purchase details, no metadata.
            Clean extraction. No trace left behind.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

